{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk to you today about prosperity,"},{"time":3000,"text":"about our hopes"},{"time":5000,"text":"for a shared and lasting prosperity."},{"time":8000,"text":"And not just us,"},{"time":10000,"text":"but the two billion people worldwide"},{"time":12000,"text":"who are still chronically undernourished."},{"time":15000,"text":"And hope actually is at the heart of this."},{"time":18000,"text":"In fact, the Latin word for hope"},{"time":20000,"text":"is at the heart of the word prosperity."},{"time":22000,"text":"\"Pro-speras,\" \"speras,\" hope --"},{"time":25000,"text":"in accordance with our hopes and expectations."},{"time":28000,"text":"The irony is, though,"},{"time":30000,"text":"that we have cashed-out prosperity"},{"time":33000,"text":"almost literally in terms of money and economic growth."},{"time":36000,"text":"And we've grown our economies so much"},{"time":38000,"text":"that we now stand"},{"time":40000,"text":"in a real danger"},{"time":42000,"text":"of undermining hope --"},{"time":45000,"text":"running down resources, cutting down rainforests,"},{"time":48000,"text":"spilling oil into the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":51000,"text":"changing the climate --"},{"time":53000,"text":"and the only thing that has actually"},{"time":55000,"text":"remotely slowed down the relentless rise"},{"time":57000,"text":"of carbon emissions over the last two to three decades"},{"time":60000,"text":"is recession."},{"time":62000,"text":"And recession, of course,"},{"time":64000,"text":"isn't exactly a recipe for hope either,"},{"time":66000,"text":"as we're busy finding out."},{"time":68000,"text":"So we're caught in a kind of trap."},{"time":70000,"text":"It's a dilemma, a dilemma of growth."},{"time":72000,"text":"We can't live with it; we can't live without it."},{"time":74000,"text":"Trash the system or crash the planet --"},{"time":77000,"text":"it's a tough choice; it isn't much of a choice."},{"time":80000,"text":"And our best avenue of escape from this actually"},{"time":83000,"text":"is a kind of blind faith"},{"time":86000,"text":"in our own cleverness and technology and efficiency"},{"time":89000,"text":"and doing things more efficiently."},{"time":91000,"text":"Now I haven't got anything against efficiency."},{"time":93000,"text":"And I think we are a clever species sometimes."},{"time":97000,"text":"But I think we should also just check the numbers,"},{"time":100000,"text":"take a reality check here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"So I want you to imagine a world,"},{"time":104000,"text":"in 2050, of around nine billion people,"},{"time":107000,"text":"all aspiring to Western incomes,"},{"time":109000,"text":"Western lifestyles."},{"time":112000,"text":"And I want to ask the question --"},{"time":114000,"text":"and we'll give them that two percent hike in income, in salary each year as well,"},{"time":117000,"text":"because we believe in growth."},{"time":119000,"text":"And I want to ask the question:"},{"time":121000,"text":"how far and how fast would be have to move?"},{"time":124000,"text":"How clever would we have to be?"},{"time":126000,"text":"How much technology would we need in this world"},{"time":128000,"text":"to deliver our carbon targets?"},{"time":130000,"text":"And here in my chart --"},{"time":132000,"text":"on the left-hand side is where we are now."},{"time":135000,"text":"This is the carbon intensity of economic growth"},{"time":137000,"text":"in the economy at the moment."},{"time":139000,"text":"It's around about 770 grams of carbon."},{"time":142000,"text":"In the world I describe to you,"},{"time":144000,"text":"we have to be right over here at the right-hand side"},{"time":146000,"text":"at six grams of carbon."},{"time":148000,"text":"It's a 130-fold improvement,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and that is 10 times further and faster"},{"time":152000,"text":"than anything we've ever achieved in industrial history."},{"time":155000,"text":"Maybe we can do it, maybe it's possible -- who knows?"},{"time":157000,"text":"Maybe we can even go further"},{"time":159000,"text":"and get an economy that pulls carbon out of the atmosphere,"},{"time":162000,"text":"which is what we're going to need to be doing"},{"time":164000,"text":"by the end of the century."},{"time":166000,"text":"But shouldn't we just check first"},{"time":169000,"text":"that the economic system that we have"},{"time":172000,"text":"is remotely capable of delivering"},{"time":174000,"text":"this kind of improvement?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"So I want to just spend a couple of minutes on system dynamics."},{"time":179000,"text":"It's a bit complex, and I apologize for that."},{"time":181000,"text":"What I'll try and do, is I'll try and paraphrase it"},{"time":183000,"text":"is sort of human terms."},{"time":185000,"text":"So it looks a little bit like this."},{"time":188000,"text":"Firms produce goods for households -- that's us --"},{"time":190000,"text":"and provide us with incomes,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and that's even better, because we can spend those incomes"},{"time":195000,"text":"on more goods and services."},{"time":197000,"text":"That's called the circular flow of the economy."},{"time":200000,"text":"It looks harmless enough."},{"time":202000,"text":"I just want to highlight one key feature of this system,"},{"time":204000,"text":"which is the role of investment."},{"time":206000,"text":"Now investment constitutes"},{"time":208000,"text":"only about a fifth of the national income"},{"time":210000,"text":"in most modern economies,"},{"time":212000,"text":"but it plays an absolutely vital role."},{"time":214000,"text":"And what it does essentially"},{"time":216000,"text":"is to stimulate further consumption growth."},{"time":219000,"text":"It does this in a couple of ways --"},{"time":221000,"text":"chasing productivity,"},{"time":223000,"text":"which drives down prices and encourages us to buy more stuff."},{"time":226000,"text":"But I want to concentrate"},{"time":228000,"text":"on the role of investment"},{"time":230000,"text":"in seeking out novelty,"},{"time":232000,"text":"the production and consumption of novelty."},{"time":235000,"text":"Joseph Schumpeter called this"},{"time":237000,"text":"\"the process of creative destruction.\""},{"time":240000,"text":"It's a process of the production and reproduction of novelty,"},{"time":242000,"text":"continually chasing expanding consumer markets,"},{"time":245000,"text":"consumer goods, new consumer goods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"And this, this is where it gets interesting,"},{"time":249000,"text":"because it turns out that human beings"},{"time":252000,"text":"have something of an appetite for novelty."},{"time":255000,"text":"We love new stuff --"},{"time":257000,"text":"new material stuff for sure --"},{"time":259000,"text":"but also new ideas, new adventures,"},{"time":261000,"text":"new experiences."},{"time":263000,"text":"But the materiality matters too,"},{"time":265000,"text":"because in every society"},{"time":268000,"text":"that anthropologists have looked at,"},{"time":270000,"text":"material stuff"},{"time":272000,"text":"operates as a kind of language --"},{"time":274000,"text":"a language of goods,"},{"time":276000,"text":"a symbolic language"},{"time":278000,"text":"that we use to tell each other stories --"},{"time":280000,"text":"stories, for example,"},{"time":282000,"text":"about how important we are."},{"time":284000,"text":"Status-driven, conspicuous consumption"},{"time":287000,"text":"thrives from the language"},{"time":290000,"text":"of novelty."},{"time":292000,"text":"And here, all of a sudden,"},{"time":294000,"text":"we have a system"},{"time":296000,"text":"that is locking economic structure with social logic --"},{"time":299000,"text":"the economic institutions, and who we are as people, locked together"},{"time":302000,"text":"to drive an engine of growth."},{"time":305000,"text":"And this engine is not just economic value;"},{"time":307000,"text":"it is pulling material resources"},{"time":310000,"text":"relentlessly through the system,"},{"time":313000,"text":"driven by our own insatiable appetites,"},{"time":316000,"text":"driven in fact by a sense of anxiety."},{"time":319000,"text":"Adam Smith, 200 years ago,"},{"time":321000,"text":"spoke about our desire"},{"time":323000,"text":"for a life without shame."},{"time":325000,"text":"A life without shame:"},{"time":327000,"text":"in his day, what that meant was a linen shirt,"},{"time":330000,"text":"and today, well, you still need the shirt,"},{"time":332000,"text":"but you need the hybrid car,"},{"time":335000,"text":"the HDTV, two holidays a year in the sun,"},{"time":338000,"text":"the netbook and iPad, the list goes on --"},{"time":341000,"text":"an almost inexhaustible supply of goods,"},{"time":343000,"text":"driven by this anxiety."},{"time":345000,"text":"And even if we don't want them,"},{"time":347000,"text":"we need to buy them,"},{"time":349000,"text":"because, if we don't buy them, the system crashes."},{"time":351000,"text":"And to stop it crashing"},{"time":353000,"text":"over the last two to three decades,"},{"time":355000,"text":"we've expanded the money supply,"},{"time":357000,"text":"expanded credit and debt,"},{"time":359000,"text":"so that people can keep buying stuff."},{"time":361000,"text":"And of course, that expansion was deeply implicated in the crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"But this -- I just want to show you some data here."},{"time":366000,"text":"This is what it looks like, essentially,"},{"time":368000,"text":"this credit and debt system, just for the U.K."},{"time":370000,"text":"This was the last 15 years before the crash,"},{"time":373000,"text":"and you can see there, consumer debt rose dramatically."},{"time":376000,"text":"It was above the GDP for three years in a row"},{"time":378000,"text":"just before the crisis."},{"time":380000,"text":"And in the mean time, personal savings absolutely plummeted."},{"time":383000,"text":"The savings ratio, net savings,"},{"time":385000,"text":"were below zero in the middle of 2008,"},{"time":387000,"text":"just before the crash."},{"time":389000,"text":"This is people expanding debt, drawing down their savings,"},{"time":392000,"text":"just to stay in the game."},{"time":395000,"text":"This is a strange, rather perverse, story,"},{"time":398000,"text":"just to put it in very simple terms."},{"time":400000,"text":"It's a story about us, people,"},{"time":404000,"text":"being persuaded"},{"time":406000,"text":"to spend money we don't have"},{"time":408000,"text":"on things we don't need"},{"time":410000,"text":"to create impressions that won't last"},{"time":412000,"text":"on people we don't care about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"But before we consign ourselves to despair,"},{"time":423000,"text":"maybe we should just go back and say, \"Did we get this right?"},{"time":425000,"text":"Is this really how people are?"},{"time":427000,"text":"Is this really how economies behave?\""},{"time":429000,"text":"And almost straightaway"},{"time":431000,"text":"we actually run up against a couple of anomalies."},{"time":434000,"text":"The first one is in the crisis itself."},{"time":436000,"text":"In the crisis, in the recession, what do people want to do?"},{"time":439000,"text":"They want to hunker down, they want to look to the future."},{"time":442000,"text":"They want to spend less and save more."},{"time":445000,"text":"But saving is exactly the wrong thing to do"},{"time":447000,"text":"from the system point of view."},{"time":449000,"text":"Keynes called this the \"paradox of thrift\" --"},{"time":451000,"text":"saving slows down recovery."},{"time":453000,"text":"And politicians call on us continually"},{"time":456000,"text":"to draw down more debt,"},{"time":458000,"text":"to draw down our own savings even further,"},{"time":460000,"text":"just so that we can get the show back on the road,"},{"time":462000,"text":"so we can keep this growth-based economy going."},{"time":464000,"text":"It's an anomaly,"},{"time":466000,"text":"it's a place where the system actually is at odds"},{"time":468000,"text":"with who we are as people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"Here's another one -- completely different one:"},{"time":473000,"text":"Why is it"},{"time":475000,"text":"that we don't do the blindingly obvious things we should do"},{"time":477000,"text":"to combat climate change,"},{"time":479000,"text":"very, very simple things"},{"time":481000,"text":"like buying energy-efficient appliances,"},{"time":483000,"text":"putting in efficient lights, turning the lights off occasionally,"},{"time":485000,"text":"insulating our homes?"},{"time":487000,"text":"These things save carbon, they save energy,"},{"time":489000,"text":"they save us money."},{"time":492000,"text":"So is it that, though they make perfect economic sense,"},{"time":495000,"text":"we don't do them?"},{"time":497000,"text":"Well, I had my own personal insight into this"},{"time":499000,"text":"a few years ago."},{"time":501000,"text":"It was a Sunday evening, Sunday afternoon,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and it was just after --"},{"time":505000,"text":"actually, to be honest, too long after --"},{"time":508000,"text":"we had moved into a new house."},{"time":510000,"text":"And I had finally got around to doing some draft stripping,"},{"time":513000,"text":"installing insulation around the windows and doors"},{"time":515000,"text":"to keep out the drafts."},{"time":517000,"text":"And my, then, five year-old daughter"},{"time":520000,"text":"was helping me in the way that five year-olds do."},{"time":523000,"text":"And we'd been doing this for a while,"},{"time":526000,"text":"when she turned to me very solemnly and said,"},{"time":530000,"text":"\"Will this really keep out the giraffes?\""},{"time":533000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":535000,"text":"\"Here they are, the giraffes.\""},{"time":537000,"text":"You can hear the five-year-old mind working."},{"time":539000,"text":"These ones, interestingly, are 400 miles north of here"},{"time":542000,"text":"outside Barrow-in-Furness in Cumbria."},{"time":545000,"text":"Goodness knows what they make of the Lake District weather."},{"time":548000,"text":"But actually that childish misrepresentation"},{"time":551000,"text":"stuck with me,"},{"time":553000,"text":"because it suddenly became clear to me"},{"time":556000,"text":"why we don't do the blindingly obvious things."},{"time":558000,"text":"We're too busy keeping out the giraffes --"},{"time":560000,"text":"putting the kids on the bus in the morning,"},{"time":562000,"text":"getting ourselves to work on time,"},{"time":565000,"text":"surviving email overload"},{"time":567000,"text":"and shop floor politics,"},{"time":569000,"text":"foraging for groceries, throwing together meals,"},{"time":572000,"text":"escaping for a couple of precious hours in the evening"},{"time":575000,"text":"into prime-time TV"},{"time":577000,"text":"or TED online,"},{"time":579000,"text":"getting from one end of the day to the other,"},{"time":582000,"text":"keeping out the giraffes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"What is the objective?"},{"time":588000,"text":"\"What is the objective of the consumer?\""},{"time":591000,"text":"Mary Douglas asked in an essay on poverty"},{"time":594000,"text":"written 35 years ago."},{"time":596000,"text":"\"It is,\" she said,"},{"time":599000,"text":"\"to help create the social world"},{"time":602000,"text":"and find a credible place in it.\""},{"time":605000,"text":"That is a deeply humanizing"},{"time":608000,"text":"vision of our lives,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and it's a completely different vision"},{"time":613000,"text":"than the one that lies at the heart"},{"time":616000,"text":"of this economic model."},{"time":618000,"text":"So who are we?"},{"time":620000,"text":"Who are these people?"},{"time":623000,"text":"Are we these novelty-seeking, hedonistic,"},{"time":625000,"text":"selfish individuals?"},{"time":628000,"text":"Or might we actually occasionally be"},{"time":631000,"text":"something like the selfless altruist"},{"time":634000,"text":"depicted in Rembrandt's lovely, lovely sketch here?"},{"time":637000,"text":"Well psychology actually says"},{"time":639000,"text":"there is a tension --"},{"time":641000,"text":"a tension between self-regarding behaviors"},{"time":644000,"text":"and other regarding behaviors."},{"time":646000,"text":"And these tensions have deep evolutionary roots,"},{"time":649000,"text":"so selfish behavior"},{"time":651000,"text":"is adaptive in certain circumstances --"},{"time":653000,"text":"fight or flight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"But other regarding behaviors"},{"time":657000,"text":"are essential to our evolution"},{"time":659000,"text":"as social beings."},{"time":661000,"text":"And perhaps even more interesting from our point of view,"},{"time":663000,"text":"another tension between novelty-seeking behaviors"},{"time":666000,"text":"and tradition or conservation."},{"time":670000,"text":"Novelty is adaptive when things are changing"},{"time":672000,"text":"and you need to adapt yourself."},{"time":674000,"text":"Tradition is essential to lay down the stability"},{"time":677000,"text":"to raise families and form cohesive social groups."},{"time":680000,"text":"So here, all of a sudden,"},{"time":682000,"text":"we're looking at a map of the human heart."},{"time":685000,"text":"And it reveals to us, suddenly,"},{"time":688000,"text":"the crux of the matter."},{"time":690000,"text":"What we've done is we've created economies."},{"time":692000,"text":"We've created systems,"},{"time":694000,"text":"which systematically privilege, encourage,"},{"time":697000,"text":"one narrow quadrant"},{"time":699000,"text":"of the human soul"},{"time":701000,"text":"and left the others unregarded."},{"time":704000,"text":"And in the same token, the solution becomes clear,"},{"time":707000,"text":"because this isn't, therefore,"},{"time":709000,"text":"about changing human nature."},{"time":711000,"text":"It isn't, in fact, about curtailing possibilities."},{"time":714000,"text":"It is about opening up."},{"time":716000,"text":"It is about allowing ourselves the freedom"},{"time":718000,"text":"to become fully human,"},{"time":720000,"text":"recognizing the depth and the breadth"},{"time":722000,"text":"of the human psyche"},{"time":724000,"text":"and building institutions"},{"time":726000,"text":"to protect Rembrandt's fragile altruist within."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"What does all this mean for economics?"},{"time":734000,"text":"What would economies look like"},{"time":736000,"text":"if we took that vision of human nature"},{"time":738000,"text":"at their heart"},{"time":740000,"text":"and stretched them"},{"time":742000,"text":"along these orthogonal dimensions"},{"time":744000,"text":"of the human psyche?"},{"time":746000,"text":"Well, it might look a little bit"},{"time":748000,"text":"like the 4,000 community-interest companies"},{"time":750000,"text":"that have sprung up in the U.K. over the last five years"},{"time":753000,"text":"and a similar rise in B corporations in the United States,"},{"time":756000,"text":"enterprises"},{"time":758000,"text":"that have ecological and social goals"},{"time":760000,"text":"written into their constitution"},{"time":762000,"text":"at their heart --"},{"time":764000,"text":"companies, in fact, like this one, Ecosia."},{"time":767000,"text":"And I just want to, very quickly, show you this."},{"time":769000,"text":"Ecosia is an Internet search engine."},{"time":771000,"text":"Internet search engines work"},{"time":773000,"text":"by drawing revenues from sponsored links"},{"time":775000,"text":"that appear when you do a search."},{"time":777000,"text":"And Ecosia works in pretty much the same way."},{"time":781000,"text":"So we can do that here --"},{"time":783000,"text":"we can just put in a little search term."},{"time":785000,"text":"There you go, Oxford, that's where we are. See what comes up."},{"time":788000,"text":"The difference with Ecosia though"},{"time":790000,"text":"is that, in Ecosia's case,"},{"time":792000,"text":"it draws the revenues in the same way,"},{"time":795000,"text":"but it allocates"},{"time":797000,"text":"80 percent of those revenues"},{"time":800000,"text":"to a rainforest protection project in the Amazon."},{"time":802000,"text":"And we're going to do it."},{"time":804000,"text":"We're just going to click on Naturejobs.uk."},{"time":806000,"text":"In case anyone out there is looking for a job in a recession,"},{"time":808000,"text":"that's the page to go to."},{"time":810000,"text":"And what happened then was"},{"time":812000,"text":"the sponsor gave revenues to Ecosia,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and Ecosia is giving 80 percent of those revenues"},{"time":817000,"text":"to a rainforest protection project."},{"time":819000,"text":"It's taking profits from one place"},{"time":821000,"text":"and allocating them"},{"time":823000,"text":"into the protection of ecological resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"It's a different kind of enterprise"},{"time":827000,"text":"for a new economy."},{"time":829000,"text":"It's a form, if you like,"},{"time":831000,"text":"of ecological altruism --"},{"time":833000,"text":"perhaps something along those lines. Maybe it's that."},{"time":836000,"text":"Whatever it is,"},{"time":838000,"text":"whatever this new economy is,"},{"time":841000,"text":"what we need the economy to do, in fact,"},{"time":844000,"text":"is to put investment"},{"time":846000,"text":"back into the heart of the model,"},{"time":848000,"text":"to re-conceive investment."},{"time":850000,"text":"Only now, investment"},{"time":852000,"text":"isn't going to be"},{"time":854000,"text":"about the relentless and mindless"},{"time":856000,"text":"pursuit of consumption growth."},{"time":858000,"text":"Investment has to be a different beast."},{"time":861000,"text":"Investment has to be,"},{"time":863000,"text":"in the new economy,"},{"time":865000,"text":"protecting and nurturing"},{"time":867000,"text":"the ecological assets on which our future depends."},{"time":870000,"text":"It has to be about transition."},{"time":872000,"text":"It has to be investing in low-carbon technologies"},{"time":874000,"text":"and infrastructures."},{"time":876000,"text":"We have to invest, in fact,"},{"time":879000,"text":"in the idea of a meaningful prosperity,"},{"time":882000,"text":"providing capabilities"},{"time":885000,"text":"for people to flourish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"And of course, this task has material dimensions."},{"time":890000,"text":"It would be nonsense to talk about people flourishing"},{"time":893000,"text":"if they didn't have food, clothing and shelter."},{"time":895000,"text":"But it's also clear that prosperity goes beyond this."},{"time":898000,"text":"It has social and psychological aims --"},{"time":901000,"text":"family, friendship,"},{"time":903000,"text":"commitments, society,"},{"time":905000,"text":"participating in the life of that society."},{"time":908000,"text":"And this too"},{"time":910000,"text":"requires investment,"},{"time":913000,"text":"investment -- for example, in places --"},{"time":915000,"text":"places where we can connect,"},{"time":917000,"text":"places where we can participate,"},{"time":919000,"text":"shared spaces,"},{"time":921000,"text":"concert halls, gardens,"},{"time":923000,"text":"public parks,"},{"time":925000,"text":"libraries, museums, quiet centers,"},{"time":927000,"text":"places of joy and celebration,"},{"time":930000,"text":"places of tranquility and contemplation,"},{"time":933000,"text":"sites for the \"cultivation"},{"time":935000,"text":"of a common citizenship,\""},{"time":938000,"text":"in Michael Sandel's lovely phrase."},{"time":941000,"text":"An investment -- investment, after all, is just such a basic economic concept --"},{"time":945000,"text":"is nothing more nor less"},{"time":947000,"text":"than a relationship"},{"time":949000,"text":"between the present and the future,"},{"time":951000,"text":"a shared present and a common future."},{"time":954000,"text":"And we need that relationship to reflect,"},{"time":956000,"text":"to reclaim hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960000,"text":"So let me come back, with this sense of hope,"},{"time":963000,"text":"to the two billion people"},{"time":965000,"text":"still trying to live each day"},{"time":967000,"text":"on less than the price of a skinny latte"},{"time":970000,"text":"from the cafe next door."},{"time":972000,"text":"What can we offer those people?"},{"time":974000,"text":"It's clear that we have a responsibility"},{"time":976000,"text":"to help lift them out of poverty."},{"time":978000,"text":"It's clear that we have a responsibility"},{"time":980000,"text":"to make room for growth"},{"time":982000,"text":"where growth really matters in those poorest nations."},{"time":985000,"text":"And it's also clear that we will never achieve that"},{"time":988000,"text":"unless we're capable of redefining"},{"time":991000,"text":"a meaningful sense of prosperity in the richer nations,"},{"time":994000,"text":"a prosperity that is more meaningful"},{"time":996000,"text":"and less materialistic"},{"time":998000,"text":"than the growth-based model."},{"time":1000000,"text":"So this is not just"},{"time":1002000,"text":"a Western post-materialist fantasy."},{"time":1005000,"text":"In fact, an African philosopher wrote to me,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"when \"Prosperity Without Growth\" was published,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"pointing out the similarities"},{"time":1012000,"text":"between this view of prosperity"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and the traditional African concept of ubuntu."},{"time":1017000,"text":"Ubuntu says, \"I am"},{"time":1020000,"text":"because we are.\""},{"time":1022000,"text":"Prosperity is a shared endeavor."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Its roots are long and deep --"},{"time":1027000,"text":"its foundations, I've tried to show,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"exist already, inside each of us."},{"time":1032000,"text":"So this is not about"},{"time":1034000,"text":"standing in the way of development."},{"time":1036000,"text":"It's not about"},{"time":1038000,"text":"overthrowing capitalism."},{"time":1040000,"text":"It's not about"},{"time":1042000,"text":"trying to change human nature."},{"time":1044000,"text":"What we're doing here"},{"time":1046000,"text":"is we're taking a few simple steps"},{"time":1048000,"text":"towards an economics fit for purpose."},{"time":1051000,"text":"And at the heart of that economics,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"we're placing a more credible,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"more robust,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"and more realistic vision"},{"time":1061000,"text":"of what it means to be human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"Chris Anderson: While they're taking the podium away, just a quick question."},{"time":1078000,"text":"First of all, economists aren't supposed to be inspiring,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"so you may need to work on the tone a little."},{"time":1083000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1085000,"text":"Can you picture the politicians ever buying into this?"},{"time":1087000,"text":"I mean, can you picture"},{"time":1089000,"text":"a politician standing up in Britain and saying,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"\"GDP fell two percent this year. Good news!"},{"time":1095000,"text":"We're actually all happier, and a country's more beautiful,"},{"time":1097000,"text":"and our lives are better.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"Tim Jackson: Well that's clearly not what you're doing."},{"time":1101000,"text":"You're not making news out of things falling down."},{"time":1103000,"text":"You're making news out of the things that tell you that we're flourishing."},{"time":1106000,"text":"Can I picture politicians doing it?"},{"time":1108000,"text":"Actually, I already am seeing a little bit of it."},{"time":1110000,"text":"When we first started this kind of work,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"politicians would stand up, treasury spokesmen would stand up,"},{"time":1115000,"text":"and accuse us of wanting to go back and live in caves."},{"time":1118000,"text":"And actually in the period"},{"time":1120000,"text":"through which we've been working over the last 18 years --"},{"time":1122000,"text":"partly because of the financial crisis"},{"time":1124000,"text":"and a little bit of humility in the profession of economics --"},{"time":1127000,"text":"actually people are engaging in this issue"},{"time":1130000,"text":"in all sorts of countries around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132000,"text":"CA: But is it mainly politicians who are going to have to get their act together,"},{"time":1135000,"text":"or is it going to be more just civil society and companies?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1138000,"text":"TJ: It has to be companies. It has to be civil society."},{"time":1141000,"text":"But it has to have political leadership."},{"time":1144000,"text":"This is a kind of agenda,"},{"time":1146000,"text":"which actually politicians themselves"},{"time":1148000,"text":"are kind of caught in that dilemma,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"because they're hooked on the growth model themselves."},{"time":1152000,"text":"But actually opening up the space"},{"time":1154000,"text":"to think about different ways of governing,"},{"time":1156000,"text":"different kinds of politics,"},{"time":1158000,"text":"and creating the space"},{"time":1160000,"text":"for civil society and businesses to operate differently --"},{"time":1162000,"text":"absolutely vital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1164000,"text":"CA: And if someone could convince you"},{"time":1166000,"text":"that we actually can make the -- what was it? --"},{"time":1168000,"text":"the 130-fold improvement in efficiency,"},{"time":1170000,"text":"of reduction of carbon footprint,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"would you then actually like that picture of economic growth"},{"time":1175000,"text":"into more knowledge-based goods?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"TJ: I would still want to know that you could do that"},{"time":1179000,"text":"and get below zero by the end of the century,"},{"time":1181000,"text":"in terms of taking carbon out of the atmosphere,"},{"time":1183000,"text":"and solve the problem of biodiversity"},{"time":1185000,"text":"and reduce the impact on land use"},{"time":1187000,"text":"and do something about the erosion of topsoils and the quality of water."},{"time":1190000,"text":"If you can convince me we can do all that,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"then, yes, I would take the two percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1196000,"text":"CA: Tim, thank you for a very important talk. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1199000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}